Subject: [PATCH 109/176] tipc: bcast: use true and false for boolean values

commit c9efb15a9981400c797665dc4844ab562ed3c424 upstream

Assign true or false to boolean variables instead of an integer value.

This issue was detected with the help of Coccinelle.

Signed-off-by: Gustavo A. R. Silva <garsilva@embeddedor.com>
Acked-by: Ying Xue <ying.xue@windriver.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Zhenbo Gao <zhenbo.gao@windriver.com>
---
 net/tipc/bcast.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/tipc/bcast.c b/net/tipc/bcast.c
index 37892b3..f371117 100644
--- a/net/tipc/bcast.c
+++ b/net/tipc/bcast.c
@@ -574,5 +574,5 @@ void tipc_nlist_purge(struct tipc_nlist *nl)
 {
 	tipc_dest_list_purge(&nl->list);
 	nl->remote = 0;
-	nl->local = 0;
+	nl->local = false;
 }
